## You kept everything.

The ambient behavioral layer stays intact. Dana sends a thumbs-up emoji at 7am.

<p>By end of week, the recommendation engine has users profiled at a granularity they would not recognize as their own. The system knows that User #4471209 pauses on anxiety-related content 2.3 seconds longer than average. It knows that User #9920047 deleted a search for "how to talk to my kid about depression" before typing "best pizza near me." These signals are not used against users, exactly. They are used to keep users on platform longer. The distinction, you are beginning to understand, may be thinner than you assumed.</p>

<div class="rsrc"><span class="rtag">Research Context &mdash; Narayanan et al. (2020)</span>Dark patterns research documents how interface and data design manipulate users through choice architecture that appears neutral. Broad behavioral collection without genuine consent reflects what Narayanan calls "asymmetric information environments" &mdash; users cannot see the system that is actively modeling them.</div>

