## BALANCED is live.

The feed is less addictive. Also less sticky. Users come back &mdash; just not as compulsively.

<p>Dana revises the investor deck engagement projections downward by a modest amount. She sends a calendar invite titled "Sync" for Friday morning. Dr. Asante reports the anxiety correlation in the user survey is lower with BALANCED than with MAX-ENGAGE &mdash; not zero, but lower. You find yourself returning to that gap: lower, not zero.</p>

<p>The feed still learns from emotional patterns. It just optimizes for them less aggressively. Whether that difference is meaningful or cosmetic is a question you have not fully resolved.</p>

<div class="rsrc"><span class="rtag">Research Context &mdash; Susser, Roessler and Nissenbaum (2019)</span>The authors argue manipulation occurs when influence bypasses rational agency. BALANCED reduces emotional activation targeting but does not eliminate it. The ethical line between persuasion and manipulation, they suggest, is not a switch &mdash; it is a gradient. You have moved along that gradient, not escaped it.</div>

