## MAX-ENGAGE is live.

Session times climb. The feed learns. It gets very good, very fast.

<p>By Thursday, average session length is 54 minutes. Dana adds the numbers to the investor deck with a green arrow. The algorithm has inferred that User #4471209's anxiety about their job makes them 34% more likely to keep scrolling if shown career-competition content. It learned this without being instructed to. It found the pattern in the data. That is what optimization means, at scale.</p>

<p>Dr. Asante sends a message at 11pm: "The anxiety signal is getting stronger, not weaker. I just wanted you to know." You read it. You do not respond.</p>

<div class="rsrc"><span class="rtag">Research Context &mdash; K.G.M. v. Meta et al. (2026)</span>This litigation argues that recommendation systems contributed to measurable user harm through addictive design, and that internal research documenting these harms was not disclosed. The plaintiffs' central claim: it is not capability that matters, it is awareness and choice. Dr. Asante's note is now in your sent folder.</div>

