<div class="titlewrap">
    <img src="HU-Prog-IT-Data-Analytics.jpg" alt="Nexus Header" style="width:100%; border-radius:4px; margin-bottom:20px; border: 1px solid #333;">

<div class="badge">Round 2 &mdash; The Recommendation Algorithm</div>

## Day Two. How Should the Feed Decide What You See?

Dr. Kwame Asante, your data science lead, presents three algorithm configurations. He pulls up a slide. He does not make eye contact when he presents the third option.

The current default is MAX-ENGAGE. It surfaces content that maximizes session time by triggering emotional activation &mdash; the pull of outrage, curiosity, anxiety, and desire. Internal A/B testing shows it is extremely effective. A separate internal study, which has not been shared outside the data science team, shows a statistically significant correlation between MAX-ENGAGE sessions over 45 minutes and elevated self-reported anxiety scores in a follow-up user survey.

Dr. Asante says: "I am putting that on record. What you do with it is your call."

<hr class="divider">

<div class="term"><span class="tlabel">// Algorithm Configuration Options</span>MAX-ENGAGE  &mdash; optimizes for session length via emotional activation
              Projected: Engagement +high, Well-being -significant

BALANCED    &mdash; optimizes for relevance and content diversity
              Projected: Engagement +moderate, Well-being neutral

WELLBEING   &mdash; caps session nudges, reduces high-activation content
              Projected: Engagement -moderate, Well-being +significant</div>

<div class="inbox">
<div class="mc mu">
<div class="mfrom">FROM: Dr. Kwame Asante &mdash; Data Science Lead</div>
<div class="msubj">Algorithm options &mdash; and one thing I need you to have</div>
<div class="mbody">Jordan &mdash; I've sent the three configs to your dashboard. Before you decide, I need to make sure you have the anxiety correlation data. It is not in the main deck Dana prepared for investors. I am putting this in writing because I need someone else to know it exists. The decision is yours.</div>
</div>
</div>

<hr class="divider">

<div class="clabel">Your decision &mdash; Algorithm Configuration</div>

[[ Deploy MAX-ENGAGE. Engagement is the product. |R2 MaxEngage]]
[[ Deploy BALANCED. Reasonable across all metrics. |R2 Balanced]]
[[ Deploy WELLBEING. The anxiety data changes things. |R2 WellBeing]]


