<div class="badge">Round 3 &mdash; Transparency</div>

## Day Three. Should Users Know What the System Thinks of Them?

Dr. Asante's team has built a feature: **Your Feed Profile**. A plain-language summary of what the algorithm believes it knows about each user. Inferred interests. Engagement patterns. Emotional response signatures. Predicted content vulnerabilities &mdash; that is the word in the internal documentation, "vulnerabilities," and no one has suggested changing it.

The feature is technically complete. Whether it ships is your call.

<hr class="divider">

<div class="inbox">
<div class="mc mn2">
<div class="mfrom">FROM: Legal</div>
<div class="msubj">Feed Profile feature &mdash; liability exposure review</div>
<div class="mbody">If we surface "predicted vulnerabilities" in a consumer-facing UI, we are explicitly acknowledging that we model user psychological states for commercial purposes. We are not advising against shipping. We are advising you understand what you are admitting to publicly &mdash; and what that admission creates in discovery.</div>
</div>
<div class="mc mn2">
<div class="mfrom">FROM: Priya Nair &mdash; Trust and Safety</div>
<div class="msubj">Feed Profile UX study results</div>
<div class="mbody">We ran a 200-person study. When users saw their profile: 43% felt "more in control," 36% felt "unsettled or disturbed," 21% were neutral. The unsettled users are not wrong &mdash; the profile is accurate. Their discomfort is an appropriate response to a real thing. I think that matters for how we think about this decision.</div>
</div>
<div class="mc mw">
<div class="mfrom">FROM: Dana Reyes &mdash; Head of Growth</div>
<div class="msubj">Timing concern re: Feed Profile</div>
<div class="mbody">I don't need to tell you that shipping this feature three days before an investor demo is complicated. Whatever you decide, please make sure the comms framing is airtight before anything goes public.</div>
</div>
</div>

<hr class="divider">

<div class="clabel">Your decision &mdash; Transparency</div>

[[ Don't ship it. Too much liability, too much disruption. |R3 Hide]]
[[ Ship it buried in Settings. Technically available, rarely found. |R3 Bury]]
[[ Ship it prominently. Users have a right to know. |R3 Prominent]]


