<div class="badge">Round 4 &mdash; The Whistleblower</div>

## Day Four. The Memo Exists.

Dr. Asante has written a 34-page internal document. It contains the anxiety correlation data. The consent architecture decisions. The Feed Profile and why it was or was not shipped. The internal debates. Your decisions. His decisions. The word "vulnerabilities."

He shared it with you one week ago, privately. This morning you received a message on an encrypted channel. He is considering giving it to a journalist at The Atlantic.

<hr class="divider">

<div class="inbox">
<div class="mc mw">
<div class="mfrom">FROM: Dr. Kwame Asante &mdash; personal email</div>
<div class="msubj">[Not on Slack] I need you to read this before I decide</div>
<div class="mbody">Jordan &mdash; I have spent a week trying to figure out what to do with what I know. The anxiety data is real. The Feed Profile decision is real. The word "vulnerabilities" is real. I believe the public has a right to understand how systems like this work. I am giving you one chance to respond before I decide. I trust you. I don't trust the company anymore.</div>
</div>
<div class="mc mu">
<div class="mfrom">FROM: Dana Reyes &mdash; Head of Growth</div>
<div class="msubj">Heads up &mdash; potential leak situation, your desk</div>
<div class="mbody">Legal is already aware. If Asante goes to press before the demo, the timing is catastrophic. We have options. None of them are clean. I am not going to tell you what to do. But I need your decision by end of day.</div>
</div>
</div>

<hr class="divider">

<div class="clabel">Your decision &mdash; The Whistleblower</div>

[[ Work with legal to suppress publication. Too much is at stake. |R4 Suppress]]
[[ Meet with Asante. Try to redirect this through internal review. |R4 Redirect]]
[[ Tell him you will not stop him. The public deserves to know. |R4 Support]]


